text.tspan: Stradling the borders of British Columbia, Alberta and Northwest territories, is
Canada's largest contiguous fire of 2023. The fire is estimate to be over 541,766 ha.
That area is more than double the size of Luxemourg.

tspan.tspan: Created by Cyrille Mdard de Chardon as
This region depicts unceded territory of the Dene Tha, Denendeh, Michif
Piyii, Dehcho Dene, and Dnndeh People (Source: https://native-land.ca/).
